Program: Outlook
Title: 09/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00j8sxg
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 10 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, the African migrant who survived a horrendous boat journey from Libya to Italy on which 63 others died. Also the American muslim fighting extremism in his own community. And the British man who's broken the taboo to talk about his life-threatening eating disorder. He describes how he went from five-and-a-half-stone anorexic to marathon runner. Show less